    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-25T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-25T06:00:00-05:00" n="548"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-25T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 25, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 25—7:32
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>186. Paragraph 1 of the Department’s 87, April 20, 5 p.m., was orally conveyed to
                    Chief of Far Eastern Division, Foreign Office, who duly expressed his
                    appreciation.</p>
                <p>As regards paragraph 2 (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) Foreign Office stated that when
                    the selection of a financial expert, as explained by Fisher to Atherton, is
                    determined he will be attached to the British Legation in Peiping. Paragraph
                        (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) Foreign Office has received no reply from
                    Japanese or any other Government. Paragraph (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) Foreign
                    Office stated that this question “is being handled informally by Fisher and not
                    in the usual way” but the position of the British Government is clearly set
                    forth in the note written by Fisher<note n="86" xml:id="d548fn86">Not
                        printed.</note> (forwarded with Embassy’s despatch No. 1365, April 12)
                    copies of which have been handed to Japanese and French representatives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
